  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "Table culture is the set of shared norms, habits, and expectations that govern how players interact during a [tabletop role-playing game](../index.md). Every group develops its own table culture, whether consciously or not: how much crosstalk is acceptable, whether players use character voices, how phones are handled, who brings snacks, and how disagreements about rules are resolved.",
